  description="A practical reference on multithreading: threads vs processes, race conditions (with code), locks and deadlocks, concurrency vs parallelism, async vs threads, Python's GIL, and how to write code that is actually thread-safe."
  path="/multithreading-explained"
  eyebrow="Knowledge Base · Concurrency"
  h1="Multithreading &amp; concurrency explained"
  tagline="Threads vs processes, the race conditions that bite you, how locks and deadlocks work, the GIL, and how to write code that is actually thread-safe, with real examples."
>
  <nav class="toc" aria-label="On this page">
    <span class="toc-h">On this page</span>
